animal.description: I AM ON HOLD PENDING AN ADOPTION APPOINTMENT. Little Scotty is a handsome 2-month-old boy who currently weighs about 11 pounds. We think he will grow to be 45 to 55 pounds as an adult. A perfect day for Scotty would include a trip to puppy socialization class, a nice walk with his favorite person, and lots of cuddles. Scotty's adoption fee is $350 and he is a SHELTER HERO! Which means 100% of his adoption fee goes towards other animals in the shelter. He is neutered and microchipped and has age-appropriate vaccinations. A licensing/microchip fee may apply. To meet Scotty or to be added to his waitlist, call (505) 983-4309 x 1610 and leave a voicemail message that includes the PUPPY'S NAME, plus YOUR NAME and A GOOD PHONE NUMBER - OR e-mail this information to adoption@sfhumanesociety.org. A scheduler will call you back within 48 hours to confirm your request. If you have other dogs at home, tell the scheduler you would like to bring them along for a Meet n' Greet. SFAS offers a variety of excellent training classes, seminars and Trainer Talks led by animal behavior professionals. These are $50 off for animals adopted from any shelter or rescue group! Due to current COVID-19 restrictions, classes and talks are all presented virtually using Zoom. For course descriptions, schedules and registration, visit https://sfhumanesociety.org/our-programs/behavior-training/group-training-classes/ for classes and https://sfhumanesociety.org/our-programs/behavior-training/special-seminars-and-workshops/ for seminars and Trainer Talks.

Please note donations using the SPONSOR ME tab will not go to Fluffy Dog Rescue.

To Locate Our Application go to http://rescue.fluffydog.net/how-to-adopt.html

Our listings are updated throughout the day. If there is an applicant, it will say PENDING ADOPTION next to the dog's name. If not, please submit an Application that can be found on our site, www.fluffydog.net. 

MY AGE: approx. 9 weeks (1/30)  WEIGHT: approx. 15 lbs. (1/30) WHERE I AM FROM: AL (arrival 1/30) 

MY STORY: 

Dogs are held for two weeks after arrival date. You are welcome to apply, but applications will be processed closer to the available date.

Dogs needing foster homes are available for adoption This dog does need a foster home. Have you ever considered fostering a dog?  For more information, see the Fluffy dog rescue home page. This dog does shed and is not hypoallergenic.

HOUSEBROKEN?   GOOD WITH DOGS?  Yes  GOOD WITH CATS?unknown

ADOPTION FEE: $550

To adopt the FIRST STEP is to complete an APPLICATION. The application can be found on our site www.fluffydog.net, or by clicking on the purple Fluffy Dog Rescue wording found in the left corner of this page under the dogs name.

Our dogs are located in foster homes throughout the state. We do not have a facility. Adopters must be 24 years old.We can not adopt to families with children under the age of six. We also adopt in WI, IL, and parts of MN. Most of our dogs are strays, so the breed is our best guess.
WI License #270548.
 
Check out Fluffy Dog Wellness on our Home Page. Great Solutions to Enhance Your Pet's Health. www.fluffydog.net

Please meet Zeke!  He is a Lab mix, weighing in at 65 lbs of total cuteness!  This amazing guy was owner surrendered to us recently because he was too interested in the kitty. His original family fell on hard times during the pandemic and gave him to friends that had a kitty. He is so handsome, playful, fun and loves doggy daycare!  He loves life and cuddling on the couch is absolutely magical. He likes to help you cook, if you will let him, and he can find every morsel that you drop. He is learning commands, walks very well on a leash, but is strong and does try to pull at first, and loves to ride in a car. He will try to get out with you, just in case you need help, and riding  shotgun is super fun!  He is housebroken and crate trained. He loves to play with friends and take leisurely strolls patrolling the yard. He ABSOLUTELY ADORES TOYS, especially those that squeak and crinkle. You will most likely find him in a toy box, if given the chance.  His other favorite is snuggling with you whenever he can. He has an adorable personality, especially once he gets to know you and settles in. He can be a little shy at first, but give him a second and he will follow your lead, especially if you have treats! He loves ice cream outings, sitting by the bonfire and being your very best friend in the whole world.  He can get over a shorter fence, so leash walking or a 6 ft fence would be required. 

If you are interested in this adorable, loving, fun man, please get your apps in as fast as you can!

THE APPLICATION LINK CAN BE FOUND ON OUR PETFINDER PAGE UNDER THE PICTURE. 


ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:  Zeke
Breed:  Lab mix
Gender:  Male           
Age:  1 1/2 years old  
Weight: 65 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Yes
Vaccines: Current                      
Heartworm:  Tested negative and on Heartworm prevention. Will be retested prior to transport
Microchipped: Yes

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with dogs of various sizes, breeds and genders
Cats:  No, way too interested. 
Other Small Animals:  Unknown
Children:  Yes, He has NOT been tested with infants or toddlers, so proper supervision and introductions would be required. He lived with small children with his original family and middle age children with his second family. 

ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our animals are fostered in various locations in the a South and in New England. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers who work full-time jobs and have animals of our own, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.  

If you are interested in fostering for our organization, please complete an application.  The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture.

animal.description:
Meet Meeko! *stray hold until 1/31* This sweet snuggler came in as a stray but it seems like he belongs somewhere. Meeks loves people and already knows some basic commands. He is also already neutered. He is good with horses and is super playful!Please call the shelter at (706) 795-2868 to schedule a meet and greet.

Madison Oglethorpe Animal Shelter is a non-profit shelter serving over 720 square miles. We are open intake, meaning we can not turn away animals from either county we serve. Our shelter intakes double or triple it's capacity every month so it is essential we place animals quickly into adoptive homes. Since so many animals enter the shelter we often don't have enough volunteers to write an individual bio for each. Please feel free to call the shelter Wednesday-Sunday to inquire about the animal you are interested in. 706-795-2868.

Viewing and adoption hours at our shelter are Wednesday through Sunday from 12 PM to 5 PM. 
All adoption fees include age-appropriate vaccinations, flea treatment, deworming, and spay or neuter, microchip, and adoption packet. 
Fees:
Dogs over 4 months old: $100
Puppies under 4 months: $125. 
Cats and Kittens are $75 ($65 without microchip). 

For your convenience you can fill out an adoption application for any of our current residents at www.moaspets.com. Join us on Facebook at
https://www.facebook.com/moaspets. It's a great way to stay up to the minute on the furry 4 legged friends we have looking for a loving forever home. 
We are located at:
1888 Colbert Danielsville Rd 
Danielsville, GA 30633 
706-795-2868

NOTE: Our adoptions are first come first served, simply filling out an application does not mean the animal will be held for you, you must come meet the animal in person in order to be considered for adoption.
If you rent you must bring your lease or a letter from your landlord stating you may adopt.

animal.description:
Betty is about three months old and is a blue heeler lab super mutt mix. She is about 15 pounds and will be medium sized. She can be a little shy but will do great with older children loves people and other dogs. She is crate train but would like an active family that she can go out and do activities with. She does need work on her potty and leash training as well

Betty S have your average puppy personality: silly, goofy, sweet, loving and AWESOME.  Want to adopt me?  
Interested in becoming a forever home for Betty S? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Betty S.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Betty S the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

animal.description: Hi, I'm Ari (like Ariana Grande). I am a husky mix and am a little over 1 yr old. I am looking to find a family who will love me and take good care of me. I am still a puppy so I need a family that will be able to help me learn a few things. I still like to chew things so I will need to have chew toys or I'll find your shoes, slippers or your coffee table to chew on. I do mouth but usually play or to just get attention. When my foster family eats at the table, I really just want to be with them and will try to get their food. They are working with me on trying to get me to stay out of the kitchen when they eat but it is so hard, the food just smells so very good. I also like to put my paws up on the counter so, if you have any food up there, I will find it and eat it. I am really good on a leash. I have met a few dogs in my neigbourhood and haven't met one I don't like. I just want to play with them. My foster family has 2 cats. I don't realize that I am really big (compared to them) and I guess I scare them away with my size and enthusiasum. I do chase them when they run but I just want to play. My foster parents are working on my cat manners. At night, I like to sleep with my foster parents. I usually sleep on the floor on a nice cozy bed but sometimes jump on the bed to snuggle. I don't usually stay too long. I have never had any accidents and can go through the whole night without having to be let out. I don't like being alone and cry when my foster family leaves but I like to be cozy in my kennel and will go in and out of it all day. I am crate trained. I am so excited to give all my love to my new family and can't wait to play with you. I need a house with a fence backyard please and not an apartment or condo as I have always had that and would not be a good downtown city dog. xoox With love, Ari
animal.name: Ari

animal.description:
If you are interested in adopting this dog, please download and complete an Adoption Questionnaire from our website and email US at K-9adopt@k-9lifesavers.org
You can learn about the adoption process and find a Word, PDF and ONLINE version of the questionnaire by visiting: http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/howtoadopt/.
Dog's Name: TinBear
Estimated Breed : Lab/Shepherd Mix
Approximate Age: 2-3 years
Approximate Weight: approx. 96 lbs
Currently Living at: Boarding
Adoption Fee: $300
DOG'S DESCRIPTION
This 96 pounder is nothing but a big cuddlebug. TinBear would love to find a loving family that knows how to handle large dogs. He would need space to get his exercise, so an apartment setting is not ideal.
Your new pet will require a refresher in house-training. K-9 Lifesavers strongly recommends all new adopters enroll their new pet into obedience training. This provides for an easier transition into a new home, ensures the dog remains well socialized, and helps form a bond between the dog and the new family.
Adoption fees cover basic vetting, spay/neuter surgery (for dogs over 6 months old), rabies, distemper/parvo vaccinations, treatment for worms, heartworm testing, monthly heartworm prevention and monthly flea/tick prevention (while the animal is in our care), and transport costs from high-kill shelter. Please note that on average, K-9 Lifesavers spend significantly more on each dog than their adoption fee. Adoption fee for HW positive dog also covers heartworm treatment at our partner vets.
Foster Program: Foster homes provide for the temporary care of a rescue until the dog is placed into a loving, forever home. For more information on becoming a foster parent, and our Foster Program, visit http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/foster/ or email our Foster Coordinator at foster@k-9lifesavers.org
Sponsor Me! Make a tax-deductible donation today by visiting us at http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/donate/ . Donations help us offset boarding costs and additional medical treatment for those dogs who need it. K-9 Lifesavers receives NO federal funding and survive with your generous support!
For more information on K-9 Lifesavers, or to view a complete listing of all our Adoptable Dogs, visit our website at www.k-9lifesavers.org.
Please "like" our Facebook Page for the most current events and new dogs.
Thank you for considering a rescue dog!

animal.description:
Luigi is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Luigi is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~1 year
Weight: ~37lbs
Housebroken: Yes
Crate trained: Working on it! Takes some time to settle (10-30 minutes) and will benefit from an adopter willing to continue to work on this.
Dog sociability: Frustrated/reactive with dogs on walks. He will bark/lunge/pull when he sees them and benefits from a confident handler. He has done well off-leash with some other dogs, but can be selective of his dog friends.
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Unknown, but he is mouthy (play bites) and jumpy, so only recommended for teenagers
Ideal home: Luigi is a young active dog that will do well with an adopter committed to working on training for his adolescent behaviors and exhausting his energy in positive ways! Due to his leash behavior he would do best in a quieter neighborhood and he is not a match for a high-rise or elevator building. 

Luigi is the sweetest boy you'll ever meet! He is a one year old black lab who has nothing but love to give. He is energetic, outgoing and is always ready to play with anyone! Every morning he sets out on a mission to rest his head on everyone's laps to make sure everyone gets a bit of love. He is a dog that thrives with structure and training and will require this in his adopted home. He does well with knowing what to expect out of his day and having dedicated time for playtime, enrichment time and rest time. He will do well with an experienced handler who can continue to work on training! Give him time, acceptance, and some kibble and he'll love you forever.

Luigi's adoption fee is 300. He will be neutered, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. 

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

animal.description:
Atticus is a sweet 2 - 3 year old guy who would love to be part of a forever family.  He weighs 65 pounds and is up to date on all shots, neutered, and completed treatment for heartworms. 

The shelter that he was taken to when he was found listed him as border collie cross, but I think he has some lab in there also.  I love the way his tail curls up into more than a full circle.

Atticus enjoys wandering around outside and seeing what is going on.  Since he is young, he has a fair amount of energy, but is not hyper.  He has never tried to jump up on a person.

When he left the shelter, he did not know what Sit, Down, etc meant.  He is now pretty good at sit and down.  He is learning to sit and wait until released when his meal is served.

Atticus is completely house trained.  He enjoys curling up on the couch for an afternoon nap.  He gets along with the other two dogs at my house.  He has not shown any food aggression.

There are a couple of areas where Atticus still needs to improve.  He likes to counter surf.  Also, when he is in the front yard and trucks go by, he races along the fence line with them.

Atticus can not wait to be with his forever family !

For an application, please email me and tell me a little bit about you. 

karoline.carlson@gmail.com

animal.description:
Hi, my name is  Luke S,  I am 20lbs (I will be bigger when fullygrown), about 6 months old. I am a blue heeler/Australian cattle dog mix with maybe some super mutt thrown in for extra spice!  I am very smart and love to make you happy. I would love to go to puppy classes with you, it will be so much fun and I will be the star of the class! I am good with kids, dogs, and cats. I am a gentle soul and would need a quiet home/neighborhood to grow up in! have your average puppy personality: silly, goofy, sweet, loving and AWESOME.  Want to adopt me?  
Interested in becoming a forever home for luke S? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting luke S.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and luke S the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

animal.description: Banjo came to us as a stray.  We did a DNA test to determine his breed and characteristics...boy, were we surprised! Not a sheltie at all! Along with Catahoula and Malamute, there is also some Chihuhua (!) and Husky. Banjo is about 2-4 years old, 40 lbs and about 16" at the shoulder. He is very sweet but very uncertain and reserved.  He has jumped a 4ft fence, so he needs a home with either a 6ft fence (no chain link) or someone who will take him on frequent walks and is not gone all day.  Children scare him.  He likes other dogs and he seems to prefer women. He is curious, but after two weeks he is just now starting to trust his foster mom.  He is a work in progress but we think he will be an awesome dog and a great companion in the right home. He has had all his vetting including neuter and microchip.  Banjo is being fostered in Baltimore County, MD. Covid restrictions may have an impact on the adoption process but we are doing our best to work with interested and suitable adopters.

I am a gentle soul and would need a quiet home/neighborhood to grow up in! have your average puppy personality: silly, goofy, sweet, loving and AWESOME.  Want to adopt me?  
Interested in becoming a forever home for Daisy S? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Daisy S.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Daisy S the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

DOG'S DESCRIPTION
Chloe is a little scared, but a very sweet girl. She just raised some puppies, and now she deserves a loving home with a family that will treat her like a queen!
Your new pet will require a refresher in house-training. K-9 Lifesavers strongly recommends all new adopters enroll their new pet into obedience training. This provides for an easier transition into a new home, ensures the dog remains well socialized, and helps form a bond between the dog and the new family.
Adoption fees cover basic vetting, spay/neuter surgery (for dogs over 6 months old), rabies, distemper/parvo vaccinations, treatment for worms, heartworm testing, monthly heartworm prevention and monthly flea/tick prevention (while the animal is in our care), and transport costs from high-kill shelter. Please note that on average, K-9 Lifesavers spend significantly more on each dog than their adoption fee. Adoption fee for HW positive dog also covers heartworm treatment at our partner vets.
Foster Program: Foster homes provide for the temporary care of a rescue until the dog is placed into a loving, forever home. For more information on becoming a foster parent, and our Foster Program, visit http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/foster/ or email our Foster Coordinator at foster@k-9lifesavers.org
Sponsor Me! Make a tax-deductible donation today by visiting us at http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/donate/ . Donations help us offset boarding costs and additional medical treatment for those dogs who need it. K-9 Lifesavers receives NO federal funding and survive with your generous support!
For more information on K-9 Lifesavers, or to view a complete listing of all our Adoptable Dogs, visit our website at www.k-9lifesavers.org.

Thank you for considering a rescue dog!

animal.description:
Jazz is a 2.5 yr old attentive, cuddly, petite Border Collie mix who weighs about 32 lbs. Gorgeous, sweet and smart, Jazz loves her people and all the attention they are willing to provide.  She also loves being active outside.

Jazz is looking for a family that enjoys being outside as much as she does. She loves to go for walks, hikes, and will happily help supervise your gardening in summer. After a fun day of activity, she’s happy to chill out with her family. Her resume includes experience as a home office manager, happily napping while you work or watching squirrels out the window for signs of pending invasion.  

The perfect family for Jazz will have a proven track record of helping dogs gain confidence.  She is not sure how to behave when meeting another dog while leashed. She may erupt into barking that sounds aggressive, but is likely based in fear. Jazz meets and plays with  new dogs well when both are off leash.  

As evidenced by her behavior on leash, Jazz is unsure of new situations and we want her to learn to look to her humans for direction.  Her foster family has been walking her in a gentle leader, which is helping.  Jazz’s new family will need to enroll her in classes to help build a strong bond and help her know she is safe.

Jazz requires a fenced yard (with a preference for privacy fencing), and is not a candidate for invisible fencing. She would be best in an adult home because loud noises and unexpected events that can happen with children in the home can send her running to her crate or a safe space she has chosen in the house.

Fine as an only dog or with a friendly canine companion, Jazz is silly and playful, and very loving.  She adores her people and wants to be with them as much as possible. She currently logs many miles a day zooming around the yard with her canine foster brother.  Jazz prefers a kitty-free home. She is food motivated and very easy to train, and just needs the right family to commit to working with her.

Jazz is located in Minneapolis/St. Paul. If you think you're a good fit for Jazz, please fill out an application at hoabcr.org/how-to-adopt

As a foster-based rescue, we do not have a central facility to visit. Meet and greets with specific dogs are arranged once your adoption application (not an inquiry email through Petfinder) has been received, processed, and approved. We are located in Minnesota and adopt to an area 400 miles from Minneapolis/St. Paul.

Jazz's adoption fee is $350 + MN sales tax. She is spayed, microchipped and up to date on vaccinations

Name: Snooty

Age: Puppy
DOB: 11/4/20

Gender: Female

Breed: Lab/Collie mix

Weight: 15 lbs

Dog friendly: Yes

Cat friendly: Yes

Child friendly: Yes, gentle considerate children, please

House trained: In progress, puppy

Crate trained: In progress, puppy

Energy level: Puppy

Temperament: Playful and snugly
Requirement: Not apartment appropriate

Adoption Fee: $500+tax

To adopt, go to:

http://www.mendingspirits.org/apply-to-adopt.html

From the Foster Family: Snooty is a beautiful pup. She loves to be picked up and cuddled. She will also sit in your lap to cuddle or just lay next to you for a pet. She especially loves to get her belly rubbed. Playtime is very active. Her favorite activities are chasing a ball and tug-of-war. I believe she will be a water lover as she doesn't mind bath time. She has gotten good at using a puppy-pad in the home. She will also sit before being served her food or water. We are currently working on chewing toys rather than people during playtime. This is a normal puppy behavior and she has shown signs of being a quick learner.

About Me:

Hi, my name is Snooty.

My nickname is Snoots because my foster people say that I am not a snooty puppy.
I am super sweet and love cuddles. I nibble sometimes, but I am just playing. I also love to chew toys, since my teeth are still growing. I love laying in soft and cushiony spots. Most of all, I love being with my humans.

animal.description: Molly is a 9-month old Boxer/Shepherd mix puppy who is as full of energy as she is love.  Molly was surrendered because she was not friendly with the resident cat, however if you are a cat-free household, there is so much to love about Molly.  Molly enjoys playing fetch, walking in the woods, and cuddling.  Molly knows a few commands and is wonderful on a leash.  Molly does well meeting strangers at home as long as she can meet them outside in the yard and not inside the house.  The person or family who falls in love with Molly and adopts her will need to be aware of Molly’s household vigilance, and will need to provide gentle, positive training to help her be less protective and more personable.  Molly’s shy temperament may require more than one visit by her potential adopters; she will do best in a home with dedicated humans who can provide her with structure, and continue her obedience training.  To make friends with Molly contact Tri-County Animal Rescue Center on Facebook, call 814-918-2032, or email: contactus@Tricounty-arc.org

animal.description:
Oskar ACCT-A-82581
Intake Reason: 1/13 Stray (APO Pick Up)
Sex: Male
Age: 1
Altered: No

BITE HISTORY

Medical Observations:
1/14 (Intake Exam) -- Bloody ears; No lameness noted. Superficial bite wounds on right ear

Behavioral Observations: 
1/31 (Per Staff) -- Kennel Presentation: Easy to leash/social. At front of kennel with loose body on approach. Easy to leash and remove from kennel. No issues returning to kennel and leash easily removed.
Leash Skills: Pulls Strongly On Leash
Handleability: Aroused/Allows all handling. Quickly becomes aroused, jumping up on handler but minimal mouthing. Is friendly when aroused, seems like a very big untrained puppy but his size could make handling difficult for someone smaller when he jumps up.
TagEngages in play
Toys: No interest
Color Level: Blue
Recommendations: Running Team
1/16 (Per Volunteer) -- Oskar was easily removed from kennel and walked well through the building. Once outside he pulls heavily. We attempted a dog meet and Oskar was fine from a distance. No concerning behavior so we approached another dog and his handler to initiate the meet. Unfortunately once the other dog was within reach Oskar grabbed onto the other dogs jowls. Dogs were separated and Oskar was easily returned to kennel. No injuries to either dog visible.
1/15 (Per Staff) -- Kennel Presentation: Easy to leash/social
Leash Skills: Pulls Strongly On Leash - Would do best harnessed.
Handleability: Aroused/Allows all handling - Will jump on handler and stick his face into handler's; almost head-butting. Extremely friendly, however.
Tag: Engages in play
Toys: No interest
Color Level: Blue - for strength
1/15 (Per Foster Staff) -- Took Oskar out to the yard. Solicited attention and believes he is a lap dog and loves to hop up on handler to receive affection. Interested in toys, but did not take possession. 
1/15 (Per Staff) -- Oskar was very easy to leash and waslked well on our way outside. However, once he finished his business he rushed back to the kennels and started choking himself on the leash, he should be walked with a harness on. I had to step into the kennel to get him back in, he tried to get back out so i let him out, threw treats in and then was able to remove the leash.
1/14 (Per Staff) -- Approached kennel to adjust kennel card. Oskar greeted me at kennel front, loose body and tail wagging. He was patient as if he was waiting for me to open the kennel door. 
1/14 (Per Vet) -- Friendly; BAR
1/13 (Per APO) -- dog was not aggressive 

BITE DETAILS:
1/31 - Bite was reported as one shallow puncture wound. Updated assessment has been entered. Making Available.
1/21 - Oskar was meeting with potential adopters and 3 kids, they were outside sitting on picnic table. He was jumping up trying to see the kid, and the mother had tried to push him down as the kid was scared and started crying. He snapped at her shirt, and left one puncture wound on her arm. Drew a little blood and was treated with first aid kit. He was overstimulated by the 3 kids. Bite seemed unintentional and nonaggressive, he got very excited and mouthy and behaved very well with the kids before getting overexcited

animal.description:
This little peanut is Peanut! He is 11 months old, is neutered and is just the cutest lil' fellow! A few of his favorite things are: snuggling, cuddling, being near you, and playing with his toys! Peanut is the happiest boy. He makes all of us smile immediately! 

In his previous home, Peanut has lived with a smaller dog and he did well around him! Peanut's energetic and loves to play so we do think that pups in the home should be interested in playing, too! We haven't seen him around kitties yet. If your kiddos have been asking for a puppy friend, Peanut may be perfect for them! 

He has done very well with understanding house-training. Peanut is familiar with being crate-trained and has done well in it! He even likes to sleep in it. Sometimes he really misses you when you leave so please be willing to teach him that being alone is okay! He is a smart guy, we are sure he is capable of learning whatever you show him! 

Peanut's temperament is top-notch. He is so loving and just wants to be near you! He loves tennis balls, zooming, chewing on bones, and playing with interactive toys. 

Daily walks and interaction will be important for Peanut as he is still quite puppy-like! Give us a call at (219) 872-4499 to schedule an appointment to meet Peanut.

animal.description:
This dog is in Tennessee. Adoption Donation $200 if picked up in TN, $250 plus transport fee for out of state adoptions.

Kimber is excited to be someone's constant companion! She is a goofy 10-month-old Lab mix puppy who weighs about 45 pounds. She is sweet, playful and very food-motivated. Training should go quickly with some treats. Kimber is already crated trained and is working on house training and leash training. She knows how to use a doggie door but is still a puppy so a consistent schedule is key. She is good with other dogs and likes to run and play in a fenced yard. Her favorite spot is cuddled up next to you on the couch, or sleeping in bed with her family. Kimber loves playing fetch with stuffed squeaky toys and enjoys taking out the stuffing if given the chance. If you think Kimber sounds like the kind of fun you need in your life, please apply to adopt! Kimber will be ready to go home after 2/3/21.

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: http://aarf-tn.com/adopt/adoption-apps/

If you have questions that are not covered in the profile, visit the Pet Inquiry Form: http://aarf-tn.com/contact/pet-inquiry-form/.

THIS PET IS FOSTERED IN TENNESSEE! We do list and adopt our pets nationwide. Typical transport cost to the Northeast is $160. Due to interstate adoption regulations, we are not able to adopt to RI and MA state residents.

A.A.R.F. (All About Rescue and Fixin' Inc.) http://aarf-tn.com/ is a non-profit, 501(c)(3) no kill animal rescue organization located in the Upper Cumberland area of Tennessee. A.A.R.F. is comprised of unpaid volunteers and survives only on public donations. Thank you for thinking adoption first!

Prior to adoption, all canines and felines are spayed or neutered, have received their age appropriate vaccinations, have been de-wormed for common parasites, and have received treatment for prevention of fleas and ticks. All canines over the age of 6 months have been tested for heartworm. All canines are put on heartworm prevention as soon as possible - this means dogs as soon as they are tested negative. Puppies are put on prevention immediately. All felines, regardless of age, have been tested for Feline Leukemia/FIV. Each animal receives a health check by a licensed veterinarian prior to adoption. Anything else found will be treated by our organization prior to adoption.

animal.description:
Leroy is a 7.5 year old red smooth dachshund. He is approximately 11.5 lbs. and is at a perfect weight.

He is sweet and has never met a person he didn't like. He does well with other friendly dogs when introduced slowly. 

He lives to play ball and could play fetch all day long. He would be suitable around kids (8+), as well as men and women of all ages. He walks well on a leash and loves exercise but hates riding in the car. He would prefer a home that will let him sleep in bed with his humans. He would also prefer someone who is not gone long hours every day as he has some separation anxiety. 

He recently had his dental and is ready for adoption. He had some slightly above normal liver values that may have been attributed to his dental disease, so we started him on a natural supplement. His forever home should repeat his blood work in about 3 months to confirm things have normalized.

What's the catch with this perfect sweet boy? He needs work on potty training. He went inside the house for years and is now learning to connect the dots that he is supposed to go outside to do his business. This training will take time, although his amazing foster family is working overtime to teach him this.

Requirements for Leroy's Forever Home:

Patience and experience with potty training
Home with a yard to reinforce potty training (a dog door would be fantastic)
Someone who likes throwing a ball everyday!
Financial ability to repeat his blood work at your vet

Does Leroy sound like the dog of your dreams? Please apply on our website to be considered:

https://www.portlanddachshundrescue.org/adoptionform

animal.description: Bully's foster described him as "probably the sweetest dog I've ever met." He's a long-legged, lanky  muffin who does really well with children of all ages and people. animal.description:
Meet Nala!

Nala is a beautiful young dog that was rescued from a family that was not caring for her. She is quiet and mild mannered with adults and kids. She loves to lay on her dog bed and enjoy being with people. She is great with other dogs but not so much with cats. Nala is a year old and is healthy, HW negative and is scheduled for her spay this coming week. While we don't know her breeds she looks like a petite carolina dog /golden mix. We think she is fabulous!

Nala is currently in TN but will be transported north to New England for adoption. The adoption donation is $500 which includes a health certificate and costs for her transport north.

*Unless stated otherwise, all dogs will be spayed or neutered, on flea/tick product and heart worm prevention medicine (if older than 5 months) and micro chipped prior to adoption.

*Please note that while we do our best to accurately state the breed or breed mix of a dog, we often have very limited information to draw from. Identifying the breed without pedigrees and information on heritage can be very challenging!

If you are interested in adopting one of our animals, please go to www.angelsamongusanimalrescue.org and fill out an online adoption application. Thank you!

Massachusett's Residents: Effective September 28, 2017 a Quarantine Fee of $120 will be required  (in addition to the adoption fee) to adopt a dog that has been Quarantined. Massachusetts mandates that all dogs entering MA shall be quarantined for 48 hours in a state approved facility.

Name: Soni

Age: puppy
DOB:11/4/20

Gender: Female

Breed: Lab/Collie mix

Weight: 12 lbs

Dog friendly: Yes

Cat friendly: Yes

Child friendly: Yes, gentle considerate children, please

House trained: In progress, puppy

Crate trained: In progress, puppy

Energy level: Puppy

Temperament: Playful
Requirement: not apartment appropriate

Adoption Fee: $500+tax

To adopt, go to:

http://www.mendingspirits.org/apply-to-adopt.html

From the Foster Family: Soni is a sweetie. He is quick to run up to us for a greeting. He'll let us hold him, but is very active and would usually rather be able to run and play. Sometimes, he'll let us know he is done playing by climbing up into a lap and falling quickly to sleep. He is a tiny little guy right now, and you'll definitely want to kiss his puppy face.

About Me:
Hi, my name is Soni and I love cuddles. My foster care people say my face is so adorable. I am really active and love to play tug of war and throw the ball. I love to chew toys too. Mostly I just love attention from my humans and my sister. Sometimes I get a little too wild for my sister, but I think it is so fun when she chases after me to get the toy I stole. When I am not playing, I love to find comfortable spots to nap. I hope to find a loving family and get lots of attention and playtime.

Cha Cha was rescued in December from a neglect case where she was living in a car with 15 other small dogs.  All were malnourished and in very poor shape.  She and a few others came to rain rescue and have been in a loving foster home getting the best medical treatment, lots of love and good food!!  Cha Cha is tiny, approx 7 lbs.  she is sweet and loves to just hangout on your lap and be carried around. She is very calm, and low energy.  

All of our dogs and puppies are vaccinated, multiple dewormings, up to date with flea prevention,  and microchipped.  Chacha is spayed and has recently had bloodwork, a full dental which resulted in multiple tooth extractions.  She’s ready for her forever home.  Cha Cha is 8 yrs old.  

Dogs can be met and adopted by appointment upon approval of your completed application. 

Foster home is located in Tacoma area.  

Adoption fee is $275

animal.description:
Meet Patience (or Paddy) - a loveable puppy who is right under a year old and who's curiosity knows no end. 


This beautiful girl may be deaf but she knows how to dog with the best of them! Patience loves tennis balls and will play fetch for hours. (Seriously, she loves a ball.) Caring for a deaf dog isn't much different than any other pup -- and Patience makes it easy as she only has eyes for her humans.

It's hard not to fall in love with this sweetheart because she loves every human she meets - including children. Patience is, however, particular with her furry friends but she does get along with her foster siblings well and they love playing in the yard. Patience is crate trained, house trained and has learned to sit. We're still figuring out the leash for long walks but picking it up pretty fast. She definitely has lots of puppy energy but once she's comfortable she also enjoys some good chill time. Patience will need a family/home that is dedicated to her as she has been bounced around a lot and is deserving of her forever home. 

If you are interested in me, click Apply for Adoption!

If you're on Adopt-A-Pet or PetFinder, please visit https://www.hopeanimals.org/ to apply!


** Please note that due to COVID-19 and stay at home orders, we are not having our usual adoption events. The first step in the process is to submit an online application. Virtual meet and greets over the phone/computer will be set up before selecting the best fit for adoption. Thank you!

animal.description:
We admit being the fans of the “Longmire” TV series based on author Craig Johnson’s books. We thought the most fitting name for this young 2 year old, male weimaraner can only be named after Absaroka County Deputy Sheriff Branch Connally. Branch is athletic, tall, long legged, full tail, still has his dew claws, handsome, quiet guy but he can be a talker……yes, yes, yes, we are talking about our Husker Weim Rescue, Inc. foster weimaraner pup Branch.  
Branch enjoys 2 full meals a day, when we leave. he gets a frozen treat of a kong or a filled bone of dogfood, cottage cheese, or other good treats capped with peanut butter. A chewbone, or a dental chew rounds out his treat time. Enjoying his food & treats so much, he gets them behind a dog gate or in his secure place in the house that has windows to watch the outside world. It also includes a couch where he can keep track of the activity through the house. 
First thing in the morning, before going to bed, after eating a meal or whenever you come back home, it is time to go potty.  Sometimes when you open the back door, he will stick his head out & you can see him think, “man it’s really cold” so you need to step outside, tell him go potty then he will take off to take care of business. The same cues happen when he sees the cats wander in the neighbor’s yard. Outside, he takes off barking (sounding all tough), he heads to the corner of the yard, stands at point with this tail curled & head held high. Call his name, if he chooses to ignore, a clap of your hands with “Branch” come will bring him back into the house.  
Leash training was not a priority (heartworm positive, he was on quiet time), so he walked with his foster mom back & forth in the back yard. He pulls strong with collar & leash so recommend a harness.  Now healthy, tossing a large chuck it ball does not convince Branch to pick it up & return so foster mom gets in her fitness steps. He has learned to love hopping through the snow or performing zoomies in good weather. Branch has surprised us with understanding the commands of sit, place, wait & stay.  Give the command of lay, he sits, thinks then gives you his paw. With his meal, he gets excited, so he stands or hops on his back 2 legs, command of sit with a hand signal, wait, put the food down, give him the ok, then he eats…but watch the drool.
Branch’s has a good nose. First foster dog that learned to open the drawer holding our garbage can (quietly) lift certain pieces of garbage out and take them to his secure area. Prevention is putting a baby gate against the drawer. Because of that darn good nose, a few kitchen items have been partially eaten so now the dishes & cooking utensils are rinsed, put away in the dishwasher under Branch’s fine supervision.  The disinfecting wipes come out, countertops, kitchen drawers, appliances are wiped down, stove top is washed off & the washcloth & dishtowel are put away OUT OF REACH.  I did mention the long legs equal a long reach. You will still find him in the kitchen, the nose is checking the counter, but we have put everything away. The best car rider ever, he makes himself comfortable or will sit to watch the world go by while you drive.  Branch is learning to cuddle with foster mom on the couch but needs to learn his space. Getting on the couch he sometimes landed on top of your lap, he will cuddle with his head on your shoulder with his paws wrapped over your lap. When he melts into you, he will make your heart melt. There are times when you want him to cuddle but he it’s a no go.  He is still a work in progress. A perfect home?  Weimaraner knowledge, understanding he will start talking to you if he feels you ignore him, give him exercise, no little kids (the littles would be knocked down) he is good with other social dogs but no little ones that might make him think of cats & no, no, no cats.  Interested, fill out the adoption application at huskerweimrescue.com. When submitted, email us at huskerweimrescue@gmail.com & our volunteers will get to work processing your application.

animal.description: Carla is a doll! She was shy at first in the interaction room, but we waited patiently and she came over to us and warmed up pretty quickly. She was not interested in treats, she wanted our love! She walks on the leash pretty well, but she wasn't interested in jumping into my car. We had to pick up all 60 something pounds of her! However, once she got into the car, she was all set. She laid down and didn't move a muscle. We got home and she loved exploring the yard. We gave her a bath and I was fully prepared to be drenched, but she sat patiently and was a dream! I have a dog and they were good together for several hours, but my dog wasn't happy to share my attention. Carla may be better suited as an only dog or with a dog that is less territorial than mine. She slept in the crate all night without a sound! Once she got settled in, she was happy to lounge on the couch or floor. She did not beg when we ate and seemed to be nearly if not totally house trained. She would be a fantastic addition to someone's family. Please adopt Carla!! She deserves it and so do you. :) Laid back Loving Sweet Did okay with another dog but might need to be only dog house trained Enjoys cuddling Partially leash trained minds manners likes car ride Carla is a love bug

MEET VIOLET!  Violet is a 7-year-old Terrier/Chihuahua mix.  She's as sweet as pie, and cuddly too!  Violet likes to take walks and hang out with her doggie friends at VIDA Rescue.  She loves cuddling up in her doggy bed with other small dogs, and prefers to be relaxing indoors.  Although she's a little older, she still has pep in her step! animal.description:
Dickens is a 7 month old, dapple dachshund. He is a "tweenie" and is already 14lbs (although he could stand to lose a pound according to the vet).

This boy is very sweet but was born during the pandemic and has not been socialized with people or other dogs. He is looking for a home that has experience with anxious dogs who can be patient with him. We think he was fed table scraps, or at least a lot of dog treats, which is why he is uninterested in most dog food. His foster is working on giving him fresh delicious food that is healthy (We're happy to report he does like broccoli). His forever home will have to continue feeding fresh food and watching his weight.

He is in the "chewing" phase of his puppy hood, so all furniture look like big, fun toys to him. In addition, he is still working on his potty training (He often poops inside when it's cold or wet). Finally, Dickens is a barker- A loud one at that. He barks whenever he wants something or just wants your attention.

In summary, this lovable, sweet and playful boy is not a first-time starter dog (even though he's adorable).

Requirements:
1) Home with a securely fenced yard (no apartments will be considered due to his barking)
2) No young children (9+ years) in the home since he is a nervous dog and we don't know if he will nip.
3) The other dog(s) in the home should be calm, well-adjusted and easy going. Placing him with another anxious dog would only increase his own nervous behavior.
4) New owner should be committed to enrolling Dickens in training classes to continue his socialization and behavioral work
5) No first-time dog owners as this dog needs someone who has experience with dogs and/or the unique challenges of the breed


If you wish to be considered, please apply on our website:

https://www.portlanddachshundrescue.org/adoptionform

Please note that if you apply but do not meet the criteria listed above, you will not hear back from us telling you your application was unsuccessful.

animal.description:
One-year-old Suzie is an old soul.  She has none of the puppy-like energy you'd expect from such a young dog. Instead, Suzie, a Mountain Cur mix,  is incredibly soft and gentle.  She is timid with strangers and needs time to build trust with new people.  (Children under the age of 5 would be too much for her.)  Once Suzie knows you, she is sweetly affection-seeking. She enjoys leisurely strolls outside and doesn't pull on the leash.  Suzie is housebroken and always keeps a clean kennel overnight. Suzie does have a benign angiolipoma on her face which, due to placement, cannot be removed. It is possible that this mass could grow larger but it is benign. Because Suzie was transferred in from another rescue, we are unsure of her history or if she's lived with other animals before.  Suzie would love a quiet home to help her gain confidence.  Could it be yours?

Due to COVID-19, Friendship APL is performing adoptions BY APPOINTMENT ONLY from 9:30am - 3:30pm, Tuesdays through Sundays. WALK-IN VISITORS ARE NOT PERMITTED. To schedule an adoption appointment, please email adoptions@friendshipapl.org.

If you have kids in your family and are interested in adopting a Friendship dog please bring them with you for a meet and greet.

All dogs receive one or more vaccinations, a basic veterinary examination, are dewormed, heartworm tested, and spayed or neutered. Dogs 3 months and older are micro-chipped.

animal.description:
Gorgeous Georgia sits pretty as a peach ready meet her new forever family!

Those sweet brown eyes and sunshine smile, this 7-month old, 35 lb, Boxer mix is the sweetest, quirkiest and most intelligent girl (not to mention she has the smoothest short apricot coat!).   

PERSONALITY & BEHAVIOR:
Georgia is an incredibly smart and treat driven dog! This perfect combination makes it easy for her to excel when obedience training and already knows basic commands such as sit, lay down, stay (for short periods), shake, and is working hard on leash manners. She's also already a pro at house-training and using the crate! 

Georgia LOVES dogs and gets along with all she has been around! She's very social and friendly and tolerates cats (doesn't appear overly interested in them). She ADORES playing fetch and tug of war and has a funny, quirky and affectionate personality! 

*She's always been a hard worker and has done so well in her foster home, however, she can appear a bit skittish at times and for that reason will need consistent training/guidance when interacting/meeting children. We recommend this to be a slow process to help ease her into a new lifestyle and really grow into her full potential! 

For the moment, Georgia would do better in the house with NO children.   
. 
If you’d like more information or are interested in this precious girl, please text 4-6 photo's of your interior/exterior home and yard (including fence if applicable) to Liz at 423-320-8989.

- - - 

Please Note: Inquiries through Pet Finder may be slower to respond and the best form of communication/inquiry would be through text message at the number above. Thank you.

Search for "A PAW AND A PRAYER DOG RESCUE" on Facebook to see ALL our available dogs for adoption updated daily!

animal.description:
Tusk is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Tusk is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~2 years 
Weight: ~49lbs
Housebroken: Working on it! He needs to be kept to a strict schedule 
Crate trained: Working on it! He takes time to settle (~10 minutes) and would benefit from continued training for this
Dog sociability: Friendly! Lives with two dogs in his foster home and has been doing well. He is playful with the medium sized dog his age and is respectful with the senior chihuahua. 
Cat sociability: 
Kids: Unknown
Ideal home: Tusk is pretty adaptable to most living spaces, but would prefer to not live in a high-rise/elevator building. 

Tusk is a gentle boy who loves to please. His cuddles are A+ and with fur that soft you'll never want to stop petting him and he won't oppose. He is very playful with the young resident dog and very gentle and respectful of the senior resident dog. He self entertains with toys and bones if no one will play with him. He's smart and would love to expand his trick vocabulary. He has some tiny white patches of fur on his head and neck that looks like someone dripped paint on him and it is the cutest thing. Tusk has perfected the puppy dog eyes and he deserves everything he wants! 

Tusk's adoption fee is 300. He is up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. He will require booster vaccines at the adopter's expense. Tusk will be neutered on 3/18.

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

animal.description:
Trixie is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet her.

Trixie is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~6 months
Weight: ~27lbs
Housebroken: Working on it! She will need to be kept to a strict schedule
Crate trained: Working on it! Takes time to settle (10-30 minutes) and would benefit from continued training
Dog sociability: Friendly! Lives with a dog in her foster home and has been doing well.
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Friendly with kids!
Ideal home: Trixie is an active puppy looking for a home that can keep her mentally/physically stimulated. She is nervous on walks, so she will do best in a quieter neighborhood where she can work on this or with a backyard. She would love a playful dog pal in her home or access to doggy daycare to expel some of her puppy energy.

Trixie is a whole lot of fun in a small spotted package! She loves to play with her ball in the yard and is learning fetch. She's been learning all kinds of things here at her foster home Sit, go to bed (crate), going outside to do her business. She's quite quick running in the yard which is a fun sight to see. She likes to play with her senior foster dog friend and would love a playful dog to wrestle with her in her forever home, or nearby friends. 

One Tail at a Time requires that puppies 6 months and under are enrolled in a positive reinforcement training class within 2 weeks of adoption at the adopter's expense.

Trixie's adoption fee is 350. She will be spayed on a future date (3/4/21) and a 50 refundable spay deposit will be required. She is up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. We recommended she be retested for heart worm disease when she is about 9 months - 1 year which would be the adopter's responsibility. 

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

animal.description:
Bella Rose (aka Aster/aka Pup Pup) is a sweet 5-year old female Pit Bull Terrier mix who arrived at the HSOV on August 4, 2020 after she was picked up on State Route 339 (Veto Road) by the Washington County Ohio Dog Warden.  Bella Rose was not wearing a collar, and she was not microchipped.

Bella Rose has a shiny dark brown/brindle short smooth coat with a large patch of white on her chest, a few white toes on her paws, a long tail, and a beautiful face with hopeful trusting eyes, a black button nose, and large semi-erect ears.

Bella Rose has an affectionate disposition and a friendly 'Type A' outgoing  personality. 

Bella Rose has a rather stocky physique but isn't a large dog when you see her in person.  She weighed 49.6 lbs when she entered our shelter in August 2020 but may have gained a few pounds since then.  Bella Rose is fairly strong on a leash (especially when she sees a cat nearby).  

In compliance with the Ohio Revised Code, Bella Rose (Aster/Pup Pup) was held for three days so that her family would have an opportunity to reclaim her but nobody came looking for her :(

Since she was not reclaimed, Bella Rose/Aster went home with a foster family on August 8, 2020 who planned to adopt her after she was spayed.

But Bella Rose was returned by her tearful foster family on January 29, 2021 because she wasn't doing well with a young child in their household.  They told us that Bella Rose was the sweetest dog ever and it broke their hearts to bring her back to a shelter environment after enjoying a real home for nearly five months.  We hope that someone with no small children will fall in love with Bella Rose and adopt her as soon as she is spayed.

Bella Rose has been given rabies vaccine and has tested negative for heartworm.  She will be spayed in the near future.

animal.description:
Bruiser has an intimidating name but is a GIANT teddy bear!  He has a jolly, tolerant, and friendly attitude.  Sure, Bruiser might be a little scared at first but he warms up quickly. He LOVES people, especially when they have treats for him!  Bruiser is very treat-motivated so he's eager to learn more tricks.  He already sits on command and is housebroken.  Bruiser lived with a female dog of similar size, as well as cats.  He does try to play with the cats, so he might be overwhelming for lazy or senior felines.  Bruiser is seven years old, but you'd never know it. He's in great shape and has a real zest for life.  We think he's the bees knees and know you will too!

animal.description:
Smokey is an 8 month old Lab mix who wants nothing more in life than snuggles and a ball. He is 40 pounds and just about full grown. He gets along very well with other dogs. He lives with a dog about his size and a dachshund in a wheelchair and adapts his play style to suit to both of them. We do not know about cats. 
He knows sit, is kennel trained, potty trained, and has walked incredibly well on a leash since the day we got him. He is currently being trained on how to properly heel, as opposed to the loose leash walking near you he has been doing. He stills gets distracted by other dogs on walks but is by no means unmanageable walking past them, so he will need help with that. He is learning to wait at the door to go outside instead of rushing the door and knocking someone over. Smokey wants to please. He learned to sit and wait to be released to eat his food over 4 meals. He is a very trainable dog. He is highly motivated by praise, toys, and food so you have many options for continuing his training. He is energetic but just scratch his head or his ear a little bit and he immediately turns off and just wants to snuggle on the couch with you. He likes to be with people but will go lay by himself in the other room if he wants. We have seen no signs of separation anxiety. He will play fetch with you until your arms falls off and then hit you with those puppy dog eyes so you will throw with your other hand. 
If you are interested in this cute guy, fill out our adoption application at huskerweimrescue.com.  Please drop us an email at huskerweimrescue@gmail.com to let us know that you have applied and our volunteers will start processing your application.
animal.name: Smokey

She is uncertain but very tolerant at first. Once Boo Boo is outside and comfy, she becomes a lot more puppy-like.  She loves tennis balls, romping around and getting attention from her person.  Boo Boo is accustomed to other dogs around her size. Because she was transferred in from another rescue, we've never seen her with cats or children.  We don't know how she is in a home but we do know that Boo Boo likely wasn't walked on a leash.  She is confused by the concept and will need training. animal.description:
It's not a mistake to adopt gentle Oopsie!  She is a five-year-old beagle mix and former mama dog.  Oopsie can be nervous in new situations but quickly warms up and demands cuddles and affection.  She likes being pet and will stand on her hind legs to get closer to you.  Oopsie was transferred in from another rescue, so we're unsure of her history.  She does seem to like other dogs. We've never seen her around cats or children. Oopsie has kept a clean kennel overnight but initially may have accidents in a new home.  Although Oopsie loves being outside, she still is learning to get comfortable on a leash. Luckily, Oopsie weighs 26lbs, so she's very easy to manage. Oopsie is heartworm positive and has received her first treatment. The 2nd and 3rd treatments will be provided by Friendship to Oopsie's adopter at no additional fee.  We predict great things for Oopsie.  Can you help her realize them?

animal.description:
HELP ME!!! I'm a tiny little boy and my 2 sisters pick on me ALL THE TIME!! Get me out of here please!!

Clearly I'm adorable... but I'm 1/2 the size of my sisters Aloha and Mahalo and I really need some peace and quiet. They are a LOT to take for a tiny dude like me. I know I'll start to grow big soon, but for now, I'm kind of tiny. At first, they were hogging all the food but foster mama has made sure I get plenty of it now so I'm doing much better. My foster mama is the best.

I'm a very, very snuggly, sweet little dude. I like to lay on your lap and have you pet my head and say nice things to me. I like to play too but not as much as I like to be snuggled.

I'm hoping you'll find me cute and will want to fill out an application for me... remember... I really need to get away from these 2 crazy girls. Please help a pupper out...

Shaka is a male Lab mix (we think) and was born around 11/22/20 and currently weighs about 4 pounds.

animal.description:
Meet our good ole' country boy, Clyde! Clyde is a beautiful 3 year old bluetick coonhound from Mississippi who finds our big city animal shelter a little overwhelming, and would like to come home with you, pretty please? He loves nothing more than to cuddle up with people and try to be a lap dog, a feat given that he is a big, tall boy! He enjoys people watching out the window. A bay window would be his dream come true! He currently has an ear infection and is undergoing treatment for heartworms, which our medical staff would be happy to speak with you about. 

Clyde has shown some nervous behaviors while meeting other shelter dogs, and may prefer to be the only dog child in your life. If you do have another dog at home, we would like them to meet Clyde in our shelter before you take him home. Dogs have opinions, after all! Think you're ready to show handsome county boy Clyde the Pittsburgh sights? Take him home today!

Thank you for your interest in our adoptable animals! Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, we do require appointments to see our adoptable animals. Please complete the adoption application and a Customer Care Associate will be in contact with you. PLEASE NOTE: We ask that when you submit your application, that you are available to schedule an appointment within the next 24-48 hours.

animal.description: Hello there, my name is Penny and I appear to resemble a smaller Retriever, Labrador mix. I've weighed in to be just over thirty pounds, but I do still have some growing to do. I am still working on mastering my manners and learning not to jump up when greeting you, but sometimes I just get so excited and try to give hugs. animal.description:
Sasha is a gorgeous Great Pyrenees with maybe some Australian Shepherd mixed in. Even more beautiful in person! She just turned 1 this month and is ready for her forever home.  She was adopted by a young couple who live in an apartment which is no life for a Great Pyr so they surrendered her.  We are thrilled to now have her in the Colorado mountains where we know she will be such a happy girl.  Very friendly with people, gets along great with other dogs.  We are told no cats. 

Her foster mom says about her "What a fun dog. Sasha is a BIG beautiful dog, with big happy energy.  She is confident from the get go, warms up to everyone immediately!!   A large yard is a must for her, she runs around, rolls and plays in the snow.  Playing is her game and she often strikes play pose.  Because of her SIZE you have to watch out so she doesn't run into you.  Someone who can play with her or has another dog to play with would be best.  She  is more than interested when you are in the kitchen preparing dinner.  Her head is counter level so she can definitely see what's cooking. I let her have the run of the house, she sleeps in my room, after getting up on my bed to kiss me goodnight, gets back down and is happy sleeping on the floor next to my bed. Because of her happy go lucky attitude I feel she would adjust to her forever home whenever the right one is found---of course no hurry.”  

Sasha is already spayed, microchipped, current on her vaccinations and on heartworm preventative (negative for HW) and ready to romp!

If you would like to meet this beauty, please first research Great Pyrenees as they are not for everyone!  LuckyDayRescue.org for adoption application.

animal.description:
Lady Whistledown is the sweetest 7-8 year old Rottweiler mix, who weighs about 55 pounds (but could shed a few of her extra pounds off).

After being abandoned and living in a junkyard for several months, she is resilient. The best word that her rescuer/foster used to describe her is that she’s an angel. Every person who has interacted with her, even if it’s in passing, says how sweet she is and can’t believe where she came from. All Lady wants to do is please and be loved. 

Lady is house trained and is full of love. She is heartworm positive, but is currently undergoing the first stage of treatment and is so excited to get rid of them once and for all. Lady would do best in a home either alone or with a low energy / older dog. We are unsure about cats and we do know that she would do okay if left alone for short periods of time without having to be crated. 

Lady would be best in a family who will be patient with her slow walking and who has an abundance of extra love to give this deserving girl. Apply to take this baby girl home only if you plan to give her the best life that she definitely deserves.

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.description:
Email our cat and dog adoptions teams so that we can schedule an appointment for a meet and greet to minimize the traffic within the building. One of our team members will email or call you to schedule an appointment.
Fill out the adoption application from https://parmashelter.org/adopt/adoption-policy-fees/ and email it to us at dogadoptions@parmashelter.org or catadoptions@parmashelter.org for an appointment.

***SPECIAL NEEDS DOG LOOKING FOR SPECIAL HOME***
Say hello to our sweet boy Petey! Petey is a male Lhasa Apso mix that is 8 years young and weighs 17 pounds. This gentleman came to us as an owner surrender when his owner went to hospice. Petey's heart was broken and he was very confused when he came to the shelter. He lived with one owner his whole life. We have Petey listed as a special needs pup because of his chronic allergies and his need for help with housetraining. Petey suffers from chronic skin allergies and ear infections. Petey's skin was a mess from untreated skin allergies and ear infections when he came into our care. He is scheduled for a dental cleaning and ear treatment mid-February. His ears were swollen shut with infection. He has been in a foster home where he has gradually become happier. There is more pep to his steps. He will need to have her ears cleaned daily with an inexpensive ear cleaner. He will need weekly baths with medicated shampoo. He is being placed on prescription dog food for his allergies and will also need to be on some type of skin medication for the rest of his life, such as apoquel. While in foster care, we have also learned that Petey will need a lot of patience and help with housetraining. We believe with patience and a good routine, Petey will have fewer accidents in the home. Petey is looking for a calm household. Older children are preferred. Petey is low-medium energy level. He spends a lot of his time sleeping and sitting by his person. He is very loyal. Petey is cat and dog friendly. He can go up and down stairs with no problem and he enjoys his daily walks. He loves car rides and prefers to sit on your lap. A meet and greet with any resident canines is required. Petey will be happy with a nice comfy bed, patience and love. Petey is microchipped, vaccinated, heartworm negative and neutered. Petey's adoption fee is $85. If you are looking for a loyal companion, please e-mail: dogadoptions@parmashelter.org and arrange a meet with our gentle Petey.Like Parma Animal Shelter on FACEBOOK and help pass the word about our adoptable guests! Don't forget to share pictures with your friends! Follow us on Twitter https://twitter.com/ParmaAnimalShel

animal.description:
RINGO - A "STARR" GERMAN SHEPHERD

Come meet Ringo, a handsome well trained full-bred German Shepherd.  Ringo has all the great characteristics of German Shepherds.  Ringo is extremely intelligent, handsome, a great family dog, and very athletic.  Ringo has been through obedience training classes, and is trust-worthy in a home. 

Ringo just turned 8 years old, is in good physical health, and neutered.  While he can walk and possibly interact with larger dogs if properly introduced, Ringo can not live in a home with other animals.  He does have a high prey drive,

Although not required, Ringo would benefit from a home with a fenced in yard.   He is perfect for an active owner.   Currently, Ringo is part of our owner referral program.


Please note:

Sedona Shepherd Sanctuary's mission is to rescue adult and senior German Shepherd and mixes and find them loving homes. All of our dogs are fully vetted, up to date on all their shots

Our adoption area includes New Jersey, Delaware Valley, Manhattan, Southern New York. We may adopt to Connecticut depending on circumstances. Please visit our website at www.sedonashepherd.com.

Sedona

This guy is the best assistant. You need your trash emptied, he can do it. Lost your pen, he will find it. Need a reminder to take snack breaks... this guy will not disappoint. He is the best snuggle buddy and will keep you warm on those cold winter days. 

Ferdinand is a chill dude who does well with children 8 years and older. He is still learning his leash manners and would like a home where he can continue to build his skills. Ferdinand has some ricosuave moves and comes in a little too hot when meeting other dogs. Ferdinand would love to be the only pet in his new home with an experienced adopter that would take it slow.

Ferdinand is currently being fostered in Houston, TX. We have adopted many happy families in your area and can provide references. We use an amazing ground transport that goes to your area twice a month.

Ferdinand is 82 pounds, 3-5 years old, neutered, up to date on shots, and microchipped. Please fill out an application on our website www.goodlif3bullyrescue.org/adoption-application-1 or send an email to goodlif3adoptions@gmail.com if you are interested in Ferdinand.

animal.description:
Are you tired of working from home alone?
This guy is the best assistant. You need your trash emptied, he can do it. Lost your pen, he will find it. Need a reminder to take snack breaks... this guy will not disappoint. He is the best snuggle buddy and will keep you warm on those cold winter days. 

Ferdinand is a chill dude who does well with children 8 years and older. He is still learning his leash manners and would like a home where he can continue to build his skills. Ferdinand has some ricosuave moves and comes in a little too hot when meeting other dogs. Ferdinand would love to be the only pet in his new home with an experienced adopter that would take it slow.

Ferdinand is currently being fostered in Houston, TX. We have adopted many happy families in your area and can provide references. We use an amazing ground transport that goes to your area twice a month.

Ferdinand is 82 pounds, 3-5 years old, neutered, up to date on shots, and microchipped. Please fill out an application on our website www.goodlif3bullyrescue.org/adoption-application-1 or send an email to goodlif3adoptions@gmail.com if you are interested in Ferdinand.

animal.description:
If you are interested in adopting, please apply directly with bigdogrescueproject.org/adopt.

Available for adoption in WA and OR. Fostered in the Tacoma area. Happy is available for meet and greets to pre-reviewed applications!

Happy is approximately 5 months. He is about 35 pounds currently. He is a sweet boy who is learning how to trust people. We are loving watching him come out of his shell!

Happy is doing great with his crate training and potty training. He will need more practice with a leash though!

He gains a lot of confidence around other dogs and would enjoy having another friendly dog in his new home. He has not met cats. He has spent some time with older children, and we think he would be okay in a home with older, calm, dog-savvy kids.

He is working on crate training, potty training, and leash training!

Puppies need someone with the time, energy and patience for house-training and basic obedience. 

Puppies under 6 months of age are adopted out on a spay/neuter contract

Our adoption fee includes age appropriate vaccinations, deworming, microchipping and transport expenses. Adoption fee is $450 to help offset travel and medical expenses.

All children at home should be at least age 5 to be approved for adoption!
